Burrn Firrestorrm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umullzy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mullzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/2/01 10:38:31 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/rmulzet/eq/bearform.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How points are earned and used.</span><hr size=1> Hey Burrn,<br>
<br>
I looked and looked and looked and for the life of me can't find the post which explains this whole thing - so I will try a short explanation so you get the jist of it.<br>
<br>
We (the council - Myself, Mork, Backalley/Fielder, Leiflen and Maxamillian) felt that full random on drops during raids was wrong.  Person_01 could come to 90% of raids and get little or nothing but lose an excellent item they really want to Person02 who only comes to raids where they have a chance at loot.<br>
<br>
We felt this was wrong and something we would feel really badly about if it happened to someone that was always going out of the way to help the guild (i.e. Makes time for raids etc...)<br>
<br>
So how do you track who 'most deserves an item'?  This becomes 'merit' for many guilds but can cause a lot of problems because who really knows who has the most merit? Someone might come to every single raid we put on but because they are a quiet person, they aren't noticed as much, and therefore perceived to have less merit than someone who shows up less but is very vocal (i.e they are the Main Assist most of the time.)<br>
<br>
Therefore the point system...<br>
<br>
We take a roster of each raid - people are given points for being apart of the raid. Different raids are worth different points (i.e. Temple of Veeshan worth more than Hate) and certain mobs (i.e. Trakanon) get points because they are uber mobs.  On a Chardok raid you would get points for the raid itself and then points if we down any uber mobs (King/Queen/Prince).<br>
<br>
When something drops on a raid, we ask who is interested in the item... of the people that are interested, we chose the person with the most points.<br>
<br>
Items are worth points -- so if you get something, you lose points and often drop down the scale a couple notches in your group/class.  This ensures that people only stay the highest in their groups if they A) Are coming to WAY more raids than everyone else or B) They never get any loot.<br>
<br>
I hope that makes sense.  There are some finer details but I won't go into them here... it is all common sense for the most part and not too complicated once you get your head wrapped around it.<br>
<br>
The bottom line is that we want to make sure that people who help the guild the most get items 'first'.  It doesn't help the guild if a Trak BP goes to someone who attends one raid a month - it should go to someone who is always there banging on mobs for us.<br>
<br>
And to add...  Just because someone is new to the guild and way behind on points doesn't mean they will never get loot.  Often people already have the items dropping so things will filter down anyway. And it only takes a couple nice items to drop someone from the top of the list to the bottom.  (i.e. Raids are often around 0.2 points while BP's and Robes cost 5 points.)<br>
<br>
In this forum there are a couple lists of what certain raids/mobs/items are worth.<br>
<br>
